00:34:11,082 --> 00:34:13,277
-"can be this easy."
-Okay.

477
00:34:13,317 --> 00:34:15,547
We cut to a shot right here of this guy
by a campfire.

478
00:34:15,586 --> 00:34:18,783
We see that big fish right above
some coals, right? Close-up of the fish.

479
00:34:18,823 --> 00:34:21,053
Boom, right there! As he says,

480
00:34:21,692 --> 00:34:25,150
"Hey, buddy, I'm done on this side.
Wanna turn me over?"

481
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:27,495
That's...

482
00:34:27,532 --> 00:34:29,796
-You like it?
-Yeah, it's funny.

483
00:34:29,834 --> 00:34:31,495
It's funny.
The fish talking, it makes me laugh.

484
00:34:31,536 --> 00:34:32,696
Yeah, it's funny. It's very funny.

485
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:34,864
Fish usually don't talk. That's why it's...

486
00:34:34,906 --> 00:34:38,865
The fish with the face and the voice.
It looks like a fish. You look like a fish.

487
00:34:39,410 --> 00:34:42,345
My God, I just said that to him yesterday.
That he looked like...

488
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:44,245
His mom looks like a flounder.

489
00:34:44,282 --> 00:34:47,547
-What was it for?
-What, the fish?

490
00:34:47,952 --> 00:34:50,682
-No, the spot. What was it selling?
-Yeah, the loans.

491
00:34:51,189 --> 00:34:52,850
That...

492
00:34:53,691 --> 00:34:56,489
It's... Transferring the loans
to another company,

493
00:34:56,527 --> 00:34:58,324
it's as easy as getting
the fish out of the water.

494
00:34:58,362 --> 00:35:00,887
Good. So, does the client like it?

495
00:35:01,132 --> 00:35:03,692
-Likes it, but doesn't wanna go with it.
-Why not?

496
00:35:03,734 --> 00:35:08,262
They feel uncomfortable about saying
that it's easy to transfer your debt.

497
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:10,831
-Because...
-Because it's not.

498
00:35:10,875 --> 00:35:12,866
-It's actually a nightmare.
-It's, like, really hard.

499
00:35:12,910 --> 00:35:14,741
-It's like an impossible dream.
-It's like sudoku.

500
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:17,475
Okay, but he's not paying us
to advertise the fact

501
00:35:17,515 --> 00:35:18,914
that he has
a perfectly average product.

502
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:20,815
He's paying us to be economical
with the truth.

503
00:35:20,852 --> 00:35:23,685
So tell him from me
he's gotta go with the talking fish.

504
00:35:25,923 --> 00:35:29,017
By the way,
your daughter is really good at her job.

505
00:35:29,527 --> 00:35:33,156
-I know. That's the way she is.
-And she has great hair!

506
00:35:33,564 --> 00:35:35,464
-It's healthy.
-Okay.

507
00:35:44,275 --> 00:35:47,676
I know. Yeah, but you know what?
It was fine.

508
00:35:47,712 --> 00:35:50,840
But it would be really awesome,
I would... No.

509
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:54,280
There was a line. Sorry.

510
00:35:54,318 --> 00:35:56,878
My watch is off by an hour.
Should I change it?

511
00:35:57,488 --> 00:36:00,785
You came from New York, so,
yeah, you need to go back an hour.

512
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:02,258
Use Central Time.

513
00:36:04,729 --> 00:36:06,924
You were laughing on the phone.
That was nice to see.

514
00:36:06,964 --> 00:36:08,124
-I was?
-Yeah.

515
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:11,067
-It was just work.
-It was nice.

516
00:36:12,303 --> 00:36:14,771
-Was it the fish?
-The what?

517
00:36:14,805 --> 00:36:18,138
-The fish?
-Yeah, the client went with the fish.

518
00:36:18,509 --> 00:36:22,036
They said they should give it a name.
I said we should call it Frank.

519
00:36:22,313 --> 00:36:24,213
-Because of me?
-Of course 'cause of you!

520
00:36:24,248 --> 00:36:26,842
-No, not because of me. Really?
-Yeah. For real.

521
00:36:26,884 --> 00:36:28,909
-Frank the fish?
-Frank the fish.

522
00:36:28,953 --> 00:36:30,443
-No?
-What?

523
00:36:30,488 --> 00:36:32,183
-Hi.
-Hey.

524
00:36:32,223 --> 00:36:34,851
Hey, you should be at your desk,
shouldn't you?

525
00:36:34,892 --> 00:36:37,224
Dad, this is Tom,
one of our creative directors.

526
00:36:37,261 --> 00:36:40,753
-Tom, this is my dad, Frank.
-Hi, sir. Nice to meet you.

527
00:36:40,798 --> 00:36:43,665
-Tom.
-So, what are you up to?

528
00:36:44,268 --> 00:36:45,963
I was supposed to be heading
out of town to meet a client,

529
00:36:46,003 --> 00:36:47,436
but the train got delayed.

530
00:36:48,406 --> 00:36:50,670
-Hey, why don't you sit down?
-No, no, no, I'd be interrupting you.

531
00:36:50,708 --> 00:36:52,505
-No, it's fine. It's fine.
-Really?

532
00:36:52,543 --> 00:36:55,376
-Yeah. Sit down.
-Well, thank you.

533
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:59,847
So, do you live here
or are you just visiting?

534
00:37:00,651 --> 00:37:03,051
No, no, I'm just staying the one night.

535
00:37:08,426 --> 00:37:10,360
-Here, this is for you.
-What is it?

536
00:37:10,394 --> 00:37:12,021
-You'll see.
-Well, tell me.

537
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:15,123
No, you'll see. You'll see.
I didn't wanna send it in the mail.

538
00:37:15,166 --> 00:37:17,566
-You'll see.
-Okay.

539
00:37:17,602 --> 00:37:18,728
You know what I'm trying to do?

540
00:37:18,769 --> 00:37:20,236
I'm trying to get us
all around the same table.

541
00:37:20,271 --> 00:37:23,069
The same table.
Yeah, like we used to at Christmas.

542
00:37:25,309 --> 00:37:26,606
Are you happy?

543
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:29,440
-What do you mean?
-Are you happy?

544
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:33,406
Yeah, of course I am. I'm...

545
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:38,112
Good. Good. Good girl.

546
00:37:39,423 --> 00:37:41,288
A happy one. First one on my list.

547
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:04,043
Isn't it terrible about Alice?

548
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:09,047
-Alice?
-The storm sweeping up the coast.

549
00:38:12,056 --> 00:38:14,923
My name is Alice, so I took an interest.

550
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:21,228
-It's Greek, I think, Alice.
-Is it Greek?

551
00:38:22,333 --> 00:38:24,198
-It means truth.
-Truth.

552
00:38:27,538 --> 00:38:30,029
Yeah, well, I heard about it. I...

553
00:38:31,742 --> 00:38:34,734
I was there a few days ago.
I must have just missed it.

554
00:38:34,779 --> 00:38:38,340
-You're lucky, then.
-Yeah, well, I'm always lucky.

555
00:38:38,382 --> 00:38:40,282
I'm always lucky.

556
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:51,685
Amy, have you seen David?

557
00:38:51,729 --> 00:38:53,754
-No, not yet.
-Why not?

558
00:38:54,632 --> 00:38:56,827
Well, I had an appointment
with a guy at the prison,

559
00:38:56,867 --> 00:38:58,334
but he didn't turn up.

560
00:38:58,369 --> 00:39:00,769
And I went to the embassy
and found a lawyer,

561
00:39:00,805 --> 00:39:04,036
but he can't meet till the morning.
I've just been running around.

562
00:39:04,442 --> 00:39:06,376
Hopefully tomorrow
I'll start to get somewhere

563
00:39:06,410 --> 00:39:08,708
-and we can tell Dad.
-Okay.

564
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:11,539
Look, I'll call you as soon as
I know what's going on.

565
00:39:11,582 --> 00:39:13,550
But, listen, don't worry. Okay?

566
00:39:15,252 --> 00:39:18,221
<i>Oh, sweet morning</i>

567
00:39:18,756 --> 00:39:22,692
<i>Is your head not right</i>

568
00:39:23,694 --> 00:39:28,188
<i>Did you heed my warning</i>

569
00:39:28,399 --> 00:39:32,836
<i>This is the time of times</i>

570
00:39:33,671 --> 00:39:38,165
<i>And your head feels like your body</i>

571
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:43,775
<i>Your mind is close behind</i>

572
00:39:43,814 --> 00:39:48,012
<i>There's a teardrop on your shoulder</i>

573
00:39:48,052 --> 00:39:50,145
<i>Says this is the time of times</i>

574
00:39:50,187 --> 00:39:51,984
Could you take a picture of me
in front of this?

575
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:53,046
Yeah.

576
00:39:58,629 --> 00:40:00,096
And one more just to...

577
00:40:00,598 --> 00:40:02,793
Like... Could you... Yeah.

578
00:40:19,817 --> 00:40:22,411
Okay, everybody,
it's a new day,

579
00:40:22,453 --> 00:40:24,546
an opportunity for all of us
to make amends.

580
00:40:25,122 --> 00:40:26,612
So, why don't we start
at the beginning?

581
00:40:26,657 --> 00:40:29,421
Horns, trumpets,
very percussive in the first section.

582
00:40:29,460 --> 00:40:32,452
Strings, more energy in those bows.
Ready?

583
00:40:44,041 --> 00:40:46,601
-It's fine. I'll take you right through.
-Thank you.

584
00:40:49,647 --> 00:40:51,171
They're rehearsing right now.

585
00:42:13,764 --> 00:42:17,256
-Hey, Dad, what are you doing here?
-What am I doing?

586
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:18,928
I've come to see you conduct.

587
00:42:18,969 --> 00:42:21,164
-What are you doing?
-I'm rehearsing.

588
00:42:23,007 --> 00:42:26,465
-Aren't you conducting?
-Not today. No. I'm...

589
00:42:27,144 --> 00:42:31,240
-You're playing the drum.
-I am. It's percussion.

590
00:42:33,517 --> 00:42:35,007
It's what I do.

591
00:42:36,253 --> 00:42:41,054
-I thought you were conducting.
-Not today. I'll explain.

592
00:42:41,091 --> 00:42:42,319
I should get back.

593
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:45,258
You just walked off the stage
and nobody noticed?

594
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:48,422
Come on, stop it.
What are you doing here?

595
00:42:48,465 --> 00:42:50,990
I'm visiting. It's a surprise.

596
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:53,836
I came to spend some time
with my son, the conductor.

597
00:42:55,906 --> 00:42:59,239
-That's my cue.
-Well, get back, get back.

598
00:42:59,276 --> 00:43:00,709
Okay.

599
00:43:16,327 --> 00:43:19,694
-That's very good.
-Very good. Yeah.

600
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:22,592
Never hit a drum in my life,
but suddenly I'm very good.

601
00:43:22,633 --> 00:43:25,158
Without training, without skill,

602
00:43:25,202 --> 00:43:27,534
without all the musical talent
that you have.

603
00:43:27,838 --> 00:43:29,703
Never said I was conducting, Dad.

604
00:43:30,908 --> 00:43:34,139
Yeah, well, your mother said
you were doing well,

605
00:43:34,178 --> 00:43:37,511
that you were conducting
and composing and doing your music.

606
00:43:37,548 --> 00:43:41,746
I am doing my music. It's percussion.
It suits me just fine.

607
00:43:43,988 --> 00:43:45,615
But the drum?

608
00:43:47,257 --> 00:43:49,384
It's low pressure, and I enjoy it.

609
00:43:50,294 --> 00:43:53,752
I get to travel, the money's fine,
I got no ties.

610
00:43:55,432 --> 00:43:59,732
Everybody said that you had a talent,
that you had a future.

611
00:44:01,071 --> 00:44:03,801
People are polite, Dad. You know,
they don't always tell you the truth.

612
00:44:03,841 --> 00:44:06,366
The truth is,
I was never quite good enough.

613
00:44:10,547 --> 00:44:14,381
But all that education,
and now you're disappointed?

614
00:44:15,252 --> 00:44:16,583
I'm not disappointed.

615
00:44:17,121 --> 00:44:19,954
I'm not disappointed,
but you obviously are.

616
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:22,959
No, I'm not disappointed.
It just seems like a waste, that's all.

617
00:44:22,993 --> 00:44:25,985
Of what? What's it a waste of?
Of your telephone wire?

618
00:44:26,497 --> 00:44:28,863
No, no. It's not that. I didn't say that.

619
00:44:30,134 --> 00:44:33,126
You know, I still compose,
and I conduct in my spare time,

620
00:44:33,170 --> 00:44:35,638
but nobody wants to employ me
to do that professionally.

621
00:44:35,673 --> 00:44:37,265
That's just the way it is.

622
00:44:37,307 --> 00:44:40,299
Well, I guess I'm just saying
it's never too late. You could...

623
00:44:40,744 --> 00:44:43,975
You could keep at it
and go back to studying,

624
00:44:44,014 --> 00:44:46,448
-and I could help you out.
-It doesn't work like that, Dad.

625
00:44:46,483 --> 00:44:49,816
If it was going to have happened,
it would have happened by now.

626
00:44:50,621 --> 00:44:54,580
Besides, I'm not sure it's what I wanted.
I think maybe I was doing it for you.

627
00:44:55,292 --> 00:44:56,486
I don't believe that.

628
00:44:56,527 --> 00:44:59,860
Dad, the point is, this suits me just fine.
This is what I want.

629
00:45:03,867 --> 00:45:05,835
Hey. Hey.

630
00:45:07,404 --> 00:45:10,271
Are you managing okay at home?

631
00:45:10,641 --> 00:45:13,906
-Yeah, I'm cooking every day.
-Cooking? Yeah?

632
00:45:14,778 --> 00:45:18,236
-Do you know what you're doing?
-No, I just make it up, but...

633
00:45:19,983 --> 00:45:22,975
Well, I thought we could spend
a couple of days together.

634
00:45:23,721 --> 00:45:26,212
I... Dad, I fly to Europe this evening.

635
00:45:26,256 --> 00:45:28,918
It's a big trip.
We gotta pack up this afternoon.

636
00:45:29,393 --> 00:45:31,554
I wish I could, honestly, but you know...

637
00:45:31,595 --> 00:45:34,257
I'm sorry, Dad.
That would have been great.

638
00:45:40,204 --> 00:45:41,535
Well...

639
00:45:50,147 --> 00:45:53,446
I went to see David in New York.
Is he still at the same address?

640
00:45:54,184 --> 00:45:56,084
Yeah. I think so.

641
00:45:56,820 --> 00:45:59,584
Yeah, I want to check his address
and phone number with you.

642
00:46:00,357 --> 00:46:01,483
Sure.

643
00:46:03,093 --> 00:46:05,323
-I need some fresh air.
-All right.

644
00:46:11,368 --> 00:46:14,235
-Robert, come on. Don't smoke.
-What do you mean, don't smoke?

645
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:16,739
Don't smoke. You know better.
Come on.

646
00:46:16,774 --> 00:46:18,139
Don't smoke.

647
00:46:20,144 --> 00:46:23,341
All right, I won't smoke.
Not in front of you.

648
00:46:23,380 --> 00:46:27,316
Not if it upsets you,
but you know I do smoke sometimes.

649
00:46:27,351 --> 00:46:28,716
Just so you know.

650
00:46:29,286 --> 00:46:31,686
-Anyway, you used to smoke.
-I know I used to smoke.

651
00:46:31,722 --> 00:46:32,882
That's when I didn't know any better.

652
00:46:32,923 --> 00:46:36,086
Now I do.
Your mother made me stop, too.

653
00:46:36,126 --> 00:46:41,029
You know, I will, too, but occasionally
I do smoke. When I wanna quit, I'll quit.

654
00:46:41,799 --> 00:46:43,664
-Hey, Robert.
-Hey, Dave.

655
00:46:44,468 --> 00:46:47,062
Let me get this straight.
You worked in a wire factory

656
00:46:47,104 --> 00:46:48,935
smoking a couple of packs a day,

657
00:46:48,972 --> 00:46:53,432
but me being a percussionist
and having an occasional cigarette

658
00:46:53,477 --> 00:46:56,446
-isn't good enough for you?
-Come on.

659
00:46:58,749 --> 00:47:00,979
You know, Mom used to say,
"Make your dad proud.

660
00:47:01,018 --> 00:47:03,418
"He works so hard for us."
And I know you're not proud of me.

661
00:47:03,453 --> 00:47:04,477
I know.

662
00:47:04,521 --> 00:47:06,887
-That's not true.
-I can feel it. It's fine.

663
00:47:06,924 --> 00:47:09,586
I'm working hard here.
I'm doing the best I can.

664
00:47:09,626 --> 00:47:12,026
-Have your cigarette.
-What?

665
00:47:12,062 --> 00:47:14,394
Have your cigarette, you need it.

666
00:47:18,702 --> 00:47:20,431
No, you know what? I quit.

667
00:47:23,106 --> 00:47:25,097
-Hi, Robert.
-Hey, I just quit smoking.

668
00:47:25,442 --> 00:47:27,000
-Good job.
-Thanks.

669
00:47:28,078 --> 00:47:29,670
I'm not quitting
because you want me to.

670
00:47:29,713 --> 00:47:32,773
I'm quitting
'cause I know you don't think I can.

671
00:47:33,183 --> 00:47:36,482
-Just to make that clear, okay?
-Okay.

672
00:47:38,689 --> 00:47:41,055
Anyway, you sounded good
on the drums.

673
00:47:41,558 --> 00:47:43,958
I missed a beat
when I heard you coming in,

674
00:47:43,994 --> 00:47:46,690
bumping your bag.
You kind of threw me off there.

675
00:47:47,898 --> 00:47:51,163
Well, anyway,
what's a missed beat here and there?

676
00:47:51,201 --> 00:47:52,896
It's good, sounded very good.

677
00:47:54,438 --> 00:47:57,635
Yeah. Thanks, Dad.

678
00:48:00,611 --> 00:48:04,138
We don't see each other very often.
I wasn't trying to...

679
00:48:04,748 --> 00:48:06,807
I'm sorry, you know. I just...

680
00:48:06,850 --> 00:48:09,683
Look, you just gave up smoking.
You're gonna be a little edgy.

681
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:12,314
Is that...
Is that what it is?

682
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:16,591
-Well, anyway, I'm sorry.
-Yeah, well, I'm sorry, too.

683
00:48:19,229 --> 00:48:21,322
Hey, James,
I want to introduce you to my father.

684
00:48:21,365 --> 00:48:23,230
-Of course.
-This is James Green,

685
00:48:23,267 --> 00:48:24,859
-famous conductor.
-Hi, James.

686
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,961
This is Frank, my dad.
Very famous dad.

687
00:48:28,639 --> 00:48:30,504
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice meeting you.

688
00:48:30,540 --> 00:48:31,734
-Good luck with everything.
-Thanks.

689
00:48:31,775 --> 00:48:33,037
He's busy.

690
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:39,048
You got a girlfriend
you wanna tell me about?

691
00:48:39,416 --> 00:48:44,285
-There was someone up until recently.
-But not anymore?

692
00:48:45,122 --> 00:48:49,752
You know, she wanted to settle down.
She started talking about babies.

693
00:48:50,694 --> 00:48:53,060
It's difficult with the traveling,
you know?

694
00:48:54,898 --> 00:48:56,798
There's some girls in the orchestra.

695
00:48:57,234 --> 00:49:00,362
-I noticed.
-Yeah? You noticed?

696
00:49:00,737 --> 00:49:03,729
-I got my eye on a couple of them.
-Couple, yeah?

