I'm okay. I should get home.

928
01:06:07,763 --> 01:06:09,924
Would you be okay with that?

929
01:06:10,533 --> 01:06:12,831
Yeah. Course.

930
01:06:13,536 --> 01:06:16,972
You should do what you want.
Here, take that.

931
01:06:21,610 --> 01:06:23,703
I was thinking of flying.

932
01:06:23,746 --> 01:06:25,941
-You never fly.
-I know.

933
01:06:33,756 --> 01:06:35,121
Thank you.

934
01:06:36,959 --> 01:06:38,790
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

935
01:06:43,065 --> 01:06:45,829
You didn't really wanna eat out,
did you?

936
01:06:47,069 --> 01:06:51,472
No. I didn't. Not 800 feet above
the ground in a revolving restaurant.

937
01:07:00,282 --> 01:07:03,945
Remember when your mother
taught you how to eat spaghetti?

938
01:07:04,587 --> 01:07:05,713
Yep.

939
01:07:11,193 --> 01:07:14,526
Sometimes I pick up the phone
to dial her number,

940
01:07:15,031 --> 01:07:16,828
and then I remember.

941
01:07:19,435 --> 01:07:21,369
Keep calling next time.

942
01:07:21,437 --> 01:07:25,168
The number's still the same,
and I'm still on the other end.

943
01:07:26,175 --> 01:07:27,369
-Okay.
-Yeah?

944
01:07:27,410 --> 01:07:29,503
-Yes.
-I don't know what it is with you kids.

945
01:07:29,545 --> 01:07:30,876
You always told
your mother everything.

946
01:07:30,913 --> 01:07:35,043
You never told me anything. You were
always on the phone with her.

947
01:07:35,084 --> 01:07:38,747
I'd pick up the phone, I'd say, "Hello,"
you'd say "Hi, Dad. Mom there?"

948
01:07:38,788 --> 01:07:41,348
It wasn't that bad. It was just that

949
01:07:42,158 --> 01:07:44,786
Mom was easier to talk to
and you always worried so much

950
01:07:44,827 --> 01:07:48,194
-if everything wasn't perfect.
-No, that's not true.

951
01:07:50,199 --> 01:07:53,896
-We could just talk to Mom.
-But you couldn't talk to me?

952
01:07:53,936 --> 01:07:57,394
Well, she was a good listener.
You were a good talker.

953
01:07:57,773 --> 01:08:00,606
Well, so that's good.
We made a good team.

954
01:08:01,143 --> 01:08:02,269
Yeah.

955
01:08:04,213 --> 01:08:06,977
You wouldn't change anything,
would you?

956
01:08:08,818 --> 01:08:10,877
You pushed us pretty hard.

957
01:08:11,253 --> 01:08:14,154
No. That's not true. I...

958
01:08:16,592 --> 01:08:19,254
You didn't all feel that way, did you?

959
01:08:19,395 --> 01:08:22,228
I think David felt it the most.

960
01:08:23,599 --> 01:08:25,089
Yeah, well...

961
01:08:29,538 --> 01:08:31,301
I can see that.

962
01:08:31,974 --> 01:08:34,499
He so never wanted to let you down.

963
01:08:36,145 --> 01:08:37,373
I know.

964
01:08:37,913 --> 01:08:40,313
I was never any harder on him,
as far as I could see.

965
01:08:40,349 --> 01:08:43,375
You were all different,
and look at him today.

966
01:08:45,421 --> 01:08:47,651
Did I tell you
I went to see him in New York?

967
01:08:47,690 --> 01:08:49,055
-No.
-Yeah, he wasn't there,

968
01:08:49,091 --> 01:08:51,457
but I saw some of his artwork
downstairs in a gallery

969
01:08:51,494 --> 01:08:56,056
below his apartment. It was right there
on display. It was just beautiful.

970
01:08:56,432 --> 01:08:58,525
So look what happened to him.

971
01:08:58,567 --> 01:09:01,331
He turned out okay.
You turned out okay.

972
01:09:02,972 --> 01:09:04,769
I don't know, Dad.

973
01:09:05,174 --> 01:09:07,608
How can you say that? Look at you.

974
01:09:07,643 --> 01:09:11,170
You've wanted to be a dancer
ever since you were a little girl.

975
01:09:11,213 --> 01:09:13,738
You were gifted,
and nobody pushed you.

976
01:09:13,782 --> 01:09:16,046
-What about your plans?
-It all worked out.

977
01:09:16,085 --> 01:09:19,020
What did you wanna be
when you were my age?

978
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:21,479
I didn't have any plans.

979
01:09:21,857 --> 01:09:23,381
I just wanted to hold down a job

980
01:09:23,425 --> 01:09:27,020
and find somebody crazy enough
to marry me, like your mother.

981
01:09:28,430 --> 01:09:31,228
But when you guys came along,
things were different.

982
01:09:31,267 --> 01:09:32,427
There were opportunities.

983
01:09:32,468 --> 01:09:34,864
What kind of father would I have been
if I hadn't pushed you?

984
01:09:35,204 --> 01:09:37,729
So there wasn't anything you wanted
to achieve?

985
01:09:37,773 --> 01:09:42,369
No, I didn't really think much about it.
Never really gave it much thought.

986
01:09:42,845 --> 01:09:46,440
All I wanted to do
was just be a good father, that's all.

987
01:09:58,093 --> 01:10:00,323
So you've got your boarding pass,

988
01:10:00,362 --> 01:10:04,423
and you're all checked in,
and we know your gate.

989
01:10:05,034 --> 01:10:06,262
So?

990
01:10:07,036 --> 01:10:09,436
I'll come visit you as soon as I can,
I promise.

991
01:10:09,471 --> 01:10:13,498
I'd like that. I wanna get us
all around the same table together.

992
01:10:13,709 --> 01:10:16,542
-At Christmas?
-Or before, it's up to you.

993
01:10:16,579 --> 01:10:18,444
Great. Count me in.

994
01:10:21,116 --> 01:10:22,242
Here.

995
01:10:23,385 --> 01:10:24,818
What's this?

996
01:10:24,987 --> 01:10:27,353
I had to give it to each of you.

997
01:10:27,489 --> 01:10:30,117
-Well, shall I open it?
-No, open it later.

998
01:10:30,159 --> 01:10:32,320
-Are you sure?
-Sure I'm sure.

999
01:10:33,495 --> 01:10:34,621
Okay.

1000
01:10:36,332 --> 01:10:37,629
Okay.

1001
01:10:41,804 --> 01:10:44,295
-Be good.
-Just for you.

1002
01:10:48,677 --> 01:10:50,838
-Be good.
-I will.

1003
01:11:05,160 --> 01:11:06,593
Bye, Dad.

1004
01:11:16,005 --> 01:11:17,768
Have a good flight.

1005
01:11:43,365 --> 01:11:44,889
<i>Rosie, where's Dad?</i>

1006
01:11:44,933 --> 01:11:47,265
He's on his way home.
I just left him.

1007
01:11:47,836 --> 01:11:49,736
What did you find out?

1008
01:11:50,139 --> 01:11:52,630
David was caught buying
some drugs in a bar.

1009
01:11:52,841 --> 01:11:53,899
No.

1010
01:11:53,942 --> 01:11:55,807
He got sick so quickly
that they now think

1011
01:11:55,844 --> 01:11:57,607
he may have panicked
and swallowed some of the drugs

1012
01:11:57,646 --> 01:11:58,772
when he was arrested.

1013
01:11:58,814 --> 01:12:01,044
Is he okay?
Have you seen him?

1014
01:12:01,083 --> 01:12:03,108
Not yet.
He was taken to a hospital.

1015
01:12:03,152 --> 01:12:05,416
I'm there now,
but they're not being very helpful.

1016
01:12:05,454 --> 01:12:06,853
What do you mean?

1017
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:09,824
I keep asking if he's here,
but I can't get a straight answer.

1018
01:12:09,858 --> 01:12:13,123
Listen, the lawyer's with me
and the guy from the embassy's here.

1019
01:12:13,162 --> 01:12:14,789
I need you to call Robert.

1020
01:12:14,830 --> 01:12:16,559
I promised I'd call him
before his concert,

1021
01:12:16,598 --> 01:12:19,726
tell him what's going on.
Can you do that for me?

1022
01:12:19,768 --> 01:12:20,894
Yeah.

1023
01:12:35,751 --> 01:12:38,845
Excuse me?
How much longer before we land?

1024
01:12:39,421 --> 01:12:42,254
40 minutes, but there's a storm
so it might take a little longer.

1025
01:12:42,291 --> 01:12:43,758
-A storm?
-It's okay.

1026
01:12:43,792 --> 01:12:46,192
We go around it, not through it.

1027
01:12:46,328 --> 01:12:49,388
-Can I have some more water, please?
-Sure.

1028
01:12:55,304 --> 01:12:56,771
Excuse me.

1029
01:13:08,384 --> 01:13:09,749
Ladies and gentlemen,
the captain

1030
01:13:09,785 --> 01:13:11,685
has turned on the seatbelt sign,

1031
01:13:11,720 --> 01:13:14,848
so we ask you to please return
to your seats as soon as possible.

1032
01:13:19,928 --> 01:13:23,022
Sir, you need to push your table up.
Thank you.

1033
01:13:30,906 --> 01:13:33,466
Sir, is everything all right?

1034
01:13:42,351 --> 01:13:47,015
Okay, sir. You're gonna be fine.
You're gonna be fine.

1035
01:13:47,055 --> 01:13:49,182
Just breathe for me.
You're gonna be fine.

1036
01:13:51,894 --> 01:13:54,761
Come on, it's ready.
Everybody sit down.

1037
01:13:55,130 --> 01:13:56,927
Hey, David. Come on!

1038
01:13:58,300 --> 01:14:02,464
-Thank you.
-How come you're home, Dad?

1039
01:14:03,172 --> 01:14:06,005
-I took the day off work.
-But you'd never do that.

1040
01:14:06,041 --> 01:14:08,908
I know, but I wanted to spend
some time with you guys.

1041
01:14:08,944 --> 01:14:11,879
-Is anything wrong?
-No, nothing is wrong.

1042
01:14:12,114 --> 01:14:15,083
Well, you know,
actually there is something.

1043
01:14:17,386 --> 01:14:19,650
You know,
I've been asking myself a question

1044
01:14:19,688 --> 01:14:22,953
that's been like a puzzle,
and I can't figure it out.

1045
01:14:23,025 --> 01:14:25,357
Let's stop eating for a minute.

1046
01:14:28,597 --> 01:14:31,589
I keep asking myself
why you all lied to me,

1047
01:14:33,235 --> 01:14:34,634
all of you.

1048
01:14:34,703 --> 01:14:38,639
Amy, Jeff wore the same shirt to work
the morning after I stayed.

1049
01:14:38,674 --> 01:14:41,609
He doesn't live with you anymore,
does he?

1050
01:14:42,044 --> 01:14:44,376
He left home about 3 months ago.

1051
01:14:44,413 --> 01:14:47,211
There's another woman.
That's why Jack hates him.

1052
01:14:47,549 --> 01:14:50,143
When that man Tom came over to me
at the station and shook my hand,

1053
01:14:50,185 --> 01:14:52,517
he wanted to make an impression,
didn't he?

1054
01:14:52,554 --> 01:14:55,853
You pulled a chair up before he came
over 'cause you were expecting him.

1055
01:14:55,891 --> 01:14:57,950
Tom was waiting at the station.

1056
01:14:57,993 --> 01:15:01,861
I wanted to know that you'd met him.
I didn't want to miss the opportunity.

1057
01:15:01,897 --> 01:15:05,389
In case I get sick
and we never get the chance to meet?

1058
01:15:15,477 --> 01:15:16,774
Robert.

1059
01:15:16,812 --> 01:15:18,939
I think we should go in.
I think I felt some rain.

1060
01:15:18,981 --> 01:15:21,347
There were posters all over the city.
You weren't going to Europe.

1061
01:15:21,383 --> 01:15:24,682
You weren't even performing that night.
We could have spent time together.

1062
01:15:24,720 --> 01:15:26,278
But you lied to me.
You didn't wanna be with me.

1063
01:15:26,321 --> 01:15:30,655
No, the truth is, Dad, there are
lots of things that we don't tell you,

1064
01:15:30,692 --> 01:15:33,252
but that doesn't mean
that we want to hurt you.

1065
01:15:33,295 --> 01:15:34,990
Mom didn't always tell you everything
and you know that.

1066
01:15:35,030 --> 01:15:38,397
Don't blame your mother for this,
and wipe your mouth.

1067
01:15:39,868 --> 01:15:42,393
Rosie, the baby is yours, isn't it?

1068
01:15:45,574 --> 01:15:47,565
I was going to tell you.

1069
01:15:48,777 --> 01:15:52,543
-Go on. Tell him the rest.
-Robert, shut up.

1070
01:15:52,581 --> 01:15:55,049
-Go on. I'll tell him.
-Shut up.

1071
01:15:55,183 --> 01:15:57,151
She doesn't know
if she likes boys or girls.

1072
01:15:57,185 --> 01:15:58,914
Robert, stop it.

1073
01:16:00,255 --> 01:16:02,917
Did your mother know
you were pregnant?

1074
01:16:04,660 --> 01:16:07,322
And she kept it from me.
Why would she do that?

1075
01:16:07,362 --> 01:16:11,389
We were going to tell you,
but then Mom got sick.

1076
01:16:12,134 --> 01:16:14,398
I didn't wanna disappoint you.

1077
01:16:18,240 --> 01:16:22,643
David, do you still live in New York
at that apartment?

1078
01:16:23,445 --> 01:16:24,571
No.

1079
01:16:24,613 --> 01:16:27,013
-Then where can I find you?
-I can't tell you.

1080
01:16:27,049 --> 01:16:29,279
Tell me where I can find you
and when I can see you.

1081
01:16:29,318 --> 01:16:31,218
I don't wanna see you, Dad.

1082
01:16:31,253 --> 01:16:33,187
No, stop... Do not laugh at me.

1083
01:16:34,222 --> 01:16:35,917
Tell me the truth.

1084
01:16:36,992 --> 01:16:40,689
Wipe that smirk off your face.
Wipe the smirk off your face!

1085
01:16:40,729 --> 01:16:43,892
I have your skateboard right in the shed
over there. I know exactly where it is.

1086
01:16:43,932 --> 01:16:45,331
I'll burn the damn thing! You hear me?

1087
01:16:46,435 --> 01:16:48,995
-Don't laugh. Don't laugh. Quiet!
-A 2-by-4 with wheels!

1088
01:16:49,605 --> 01:16:53,234
After everything I've done for you,
this is all you can do is laugh?

1089
01:16:53,275 --> 01:16:56,073
When I'm asking you about something
that's worrying me?

1090
01:16:56,111 --> 01:16:58,375
Jesus! David!

1091
01:16:58,647 --> 01:17:00,512
Your mother always asked me
why I was so hard on you.

1092
01:17:00,549 --> 01:17:04,349
This is why. This is exactly why!
Have some respect!

1093
01:17:17,532 --> 01:17:21,525
-So what am I supposed to do?
-Act as though nothing's wrong.

1094
01:17:21,570 --> 01:17:23,970
That's what Mom did.
It's best for all of us.

1095
01:17:24,006 --> 01:17:26,201
I can't do that.
I can't act as if nothing happened.

1096
01:17:26,241 --> 01:17:28,641
What do I tell your mother?
What do I say?

1097
01:17:28,677 --> 01:17:31,202
Anyway, she won't ask or anything
'cause she's dead.

1098
01:17:31,279 --> 01:17:32,576
David!

1099
01:17:41,723 --> 01:17:43,020
That's it. I've had enough!

1100
01:17:43,058 --> 01:17:45,356
-I'm out of here.
-Me, too! I'm out of here!

1101
01:17:45,394 --> 01:17:46,656
Come on!

1102
01:17:48,697 --> 01:17:50,358
Tell her nothing.

1103
01:17:50,532 --> 01:17:54,161
-How can I do that?
-If you love her as she loves you,

1104
01:17:54,703 --> 01:17:57,638
then you'll tell her
what she wants to hear.

1105
01:17:57,706 --> 01:17:59,970
Tell her that we are all fine.

1106
01:19:03,338 --> 01:19:04,430
Dad?

1107
01:19:27,729 --> 01:19:31,927
At last. I finally have my family
in the same room.

1108
01:19:34,870 --> 01:19:36,394
Is David here?

1109
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,463
Rosie's here, and Robert.

1110
01:19:38,607 --> 01:19:40,404
How are you feeling?

1111
01:19:40,842 --> 01:19:43,675
-Was it a heart attack?
-They're not sure.

1112
01:19:45,514 --> 01:19:47,505
Amy, is he telling the truth?

1113
01:19:47,549 --> 01:19:50,450
The doctors are waiting
for some test results.

1114
01:19:50,485 --> 01:19:53,249
Come on. You don't have to lie to me.

1115
01:19:54,356 --> 01:19:58,019
I always find it so hard
to believe all of you now.

1116
01:19:58,693 --> 01:19:59,955
Come on.

1117
01:20:01,897 --> 01:20:04,229
They suspected a heart attack.

1118
01:20:05,700 --> 01:20:09,796
They ran some tests,
and they got the results,

1119
01:20:10,906 --> 01:20:12,965
and it was a heart attack.

1120
01:20:13,909 --> 01:20:16,673
-A mild one.
-Good. A start, at least.

1121
01:20:17,746 --> 01:20:21,238
I didn't wanna worry you
until you had a chance

1122
01:20:21,283 --> 01:20:23,911
to come to terms with what happened.

1123
01:20:24,619 --> 01:20:27,144
Well, you can worry me, all of you.

1124
01:20:27,622 --> 01:20:30,182
I'm a father of 4, I expect that.

1125
01:20:30,992 --> 01:20:35,156
I know you all have problems.

1126
01:20:36,798 --> 01:20:40,734
I know that, and I can see
you've been keeping things from me.

1127
01:20:42,170 --> 01:20:45,298
-But right now, there's something...
-Dad, maybe you should rest.

1128
01:20:45,340 --> 01:20:48,673
No, I will rest,
but I need an answer to a question.

1129
01:20:49,845 --> 01:20:54,145
You were honest with your mother,
and I want you to be honest with me.

1130
01:20:54,449 --> 01:20:57,850
It's all right. I'm okay.

1131
01:20:59,120 --> 01:21:00,747
I can handle it.

1132
01:21:01,089 --> 01:21:04,320
I... I know David is in trouble,

1133
01:21:05,026 --> 01:21:07,654
and I just wanna know where he is

1134
01:21:09,397 --> 01:21:11,627
and how soon I can see him.

1135
01:21:14,669 --> 01:21:16,967
So who's gonna tell me?

1136
01:21:17,606 --> 01:21:20,598
Why don't you take it...
Why don't you rest for a while?

1137
01:21:22,544 --> 01:21:23,943
What is it?

1138
01:21:27,816 --> 01:21:29,750
Just tell me the truth.

1139
01:21:31,353 --> 01:21:32,911
Dad, I'm sorry.

1140
01:21:36,858 --> 01:21:41,090
David died, Dad. I'm sorry.

1141
01:21:44,065 --> 01:21:46,124
No, I... That's not true.

1142
01:21:46,534 --> 01:21:49,435
-Tell me that's not true.
-I'm sorry, Dad.

1143
01:21:50,572 --> 01:21:51,698
No.

1144
01:21:51,773 --> 01:21:54,571
He moved out of his apartment and...

1145
01:21:54,609 --> 01:21:55,667
No.

1146
01:21:55,710 --> 01:21:58,008
we knew that he was traveling.

1147
01:21:58,046 --> 01:22:01,140
And then we started getting calls
from Mexico.

1148
01:22:02,050 --> 01:22:06,578
There was a lot of confusion. We didn't
wanna tell you until we were sure.

1149
01:22:07,756 --> 01:22:10,020
No, no...

1150
01:22:10,425 --> 01:22:14,191
He had a lot of problems.
He wasn't happy, Dad.

1151
01:22:14,663 --> 01:22:18,190
He's been having a tough time
since Mom died.

1152
01:22:18,233 --> 01:22:20,201
We've all been worried about him.

1153
01:22:20,235 --> 01:22:24,968
Yeah, but not for sure. I...

1154
01:22:25,573 --> 01:22:29,509
It was Mexico. It could be anyone.
It could be a mistake.

1155
01:22:29,544 --> 01:22:32,809
-It could be.
-I flew out there after you visited.

1156
01:22:33,347 --> 01:22:35,941
I flew out there after you visited, and...

1157
01:22:36,484 --> 01:22:40,545
That's why you couldn't stay.
That's why we all made excuses and...

1158
01:22:40,588 --> 01:22:44,217
No. No...

1159
01:22:44,259 --> 01:22:46,819
Not my son. That's not my son.

1160
01:22:49,631 --> 01:22:50,723
How?

1161
01:22:53,768 --> 01:22:55,998
They said it was an overdose.

1162
01:23:04,045 --> 01:23:08,505
No, not my son. That's not my son.

1163
01:23:39,381 --> 01:23:40,780
What are you gonna do
when you grow up?

